variable::get_list_index_of_value.desc:
**Name:** Get List Value Index\
**Action type:** An action that returns a value\
**Description:** Searchs for a value in a list and gets its index if found. Returns -1 on failure.

**Usage example:**
```justcode
`variable` = variable::get_list_index_of_value([`list`, `list`], "any value", "FIRST");

//Or from the object

`variable` = [`list`, `list`].get_list_index_of_value("any value", "FIRST");

//Or dry by positionals

variable::get_list_index_of_value(`variable`, [`list`, `list`], "any value", "FIRST");

//Or dry by keywords

variable::get_list_index_of_value(variable=`variable`, list=[`list`, `list`], value="any value", search_mode="FIRST");
```

**Arguments:**

| ID               | Type                                          | Description             |
| :---------- | :--------------------------------------- | :----------------- |
| variable         | Variable\[Number\]                            | Variable to assign      |
| list             | List                                          | List                    |
| value            | Any Value                                     | Value                   |
| search_mode      | Marker                                        | Search Mode             |
|                  | **FIRST** - From Start (Get First Index)      |                         |
|                  | **LAST** - From End (Get Last Index)          |                         |

